    <datafield ind1="C" ind2="5" tag="999">
      <subfield code="m">By generic, we exclude delocalized systems with rare Griffiths regions The presence of these regions causes the entanglement growth to be sublinear for which our toy model would be inapplicable This is perfectly consistent with our “operator-spreading picture”: in such Griffiths regions, transport and hence operator spreading is suppressed and so the complete scrambling within a linear light-cone assumption would not hold a modified model can be formulated to account for these effects giving rise to a different form for entanglement growth</subfield>
